<div class="content-section">
    <div class="container gamecontainer">
        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-md-4">
                <h2>(WIP) Comet Lander for Android</h2>
                <p>
                    This app is still a work in progress. Comet Lander is a homage to the classic Moon Lander game that first came out in the 1970's.
                    The app uses the LibGDX framework which helps with the physics, sprites, and touch input handling. When the game loads it randomly 
                    creates the starfield in the background each time which provides a more realistic looking background view of space.
                    The tilt of the spaceship is determined by the tilt of the device to the left or the right.
                    The ships's rotation is limited to 90 degrees in either direction because the
                    goal of the game is to land on the moon/comet surface. When touching the screen the spaceship applies thrust in the vector direction that the spaceship
                    is facing. The longer the user holds the thrust the longer the flames will be coming out of the thrusters on the ship.
                </p>
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-8">
                <video autoplay loop style="height:640px;width:360px;">
                    <source src="~/Content/cometlander-demo.webm" type="video/webm">
                    <source src="~/Content/cometlander-demo.mp4" type="video/mp4">
                    <p>Your browser does not support H.264/MP4, WEBM or HTML5 Video.</p>
                </video>
            </div>
        </div>
